Node.Caption: DialogueCarriageKarthwasten: I want to stop at Karthwasten. ( gold)

Cell.Text: Well, I know the Companions make their home here. Their mead hall, Jorrvaskr, is the oldest building in the city. | Oh, and there's a nasty feud between two families called the Gray-Manes and Battle-Borns. You'll want to be careful there. | The rest you can find out by asking the townsfolk. I'd start with the barkeep at the Bannered Mare, or the castle steward.

Node.Caption: DialogueCarriageSystemLoreWhiterunTopic: What do you know about Whiterun?

Cell.Text: It's an old city, I can tell you that. The Palace of the Kings is ancient. | It's not the friendliest place for outsiders. The Dark Elves were all forced to live in a slum called the Gray Quarter. | The Argonians can't even live inside the walls. They're all stuck out on the docks. | Still, Candlehearth Hall's got decent food and cheap bunks. You could do worse.

Node.Caption: DialogueCarriageSystemLoreWindhelmTopic: What can you tell me about Windhelm?

Cell.Text: Solitude's been the capital of Skyrim as long as I can remember. Most of the High Kings of Skyrim were Jarls of Solitude first. | Ah, let's see, what else... The Bards College is here, and the main office of the East Empire Company. | If you need it, you can get a room for a fair price at the Winking Skeever, just inside the main gate.

Node.Caption: DialogueCarriageSystemLoreSolitudeTopic: What do you know about Solitude?

Cell.Text: You can get a room at the Bee and Barb, but mind your coin purse -- it's no secret the Thieves' Guild makes its home here. | Oh, and if you meet Maven Black-Briar, stay on her good side. This is her city, and nobody else's.

Cell.Text: S|<<Shared>> What do you suppose this is all about?
This here's Rorikstead. Quiet place. Good people, though. You can get a room and a mug at the Frostfruit Inn if you care to stay.
That's the Honningbrew Meadery. Supposed to be a big rivalry between them and the Black-Briars of Riften.
S|Remember when that used to be the Honningbrew Meadery? Didn't stand a chance against those Black-Briars of Riften.
This is Karthwasten. Mining town. I hear they've had a lot of trouble with the Forsworn.
This here's the Darkwater. Comes down from Lake Honrich into the White River, a few miles downstream. Good fishing, I hear.
Morthal, capital of Hjaalmarch hold. Not quite in the same league as Solitude or Whiterun, but a nice enough place if you like swamps.
Here we are. Dawnstar. Capital of the Pale. Don't get up this way much. Beautiful country though.
I can't say I've been to Winterhold more than a handful of times. Can't see much reason most honest folk would want to come up here.
Well, this is Falkreath. Not much to look at if you're used to the bigger cities, but the folk here are friendly enough if you give them a chance.
The Braidwood Inn's up that way. I know the innkeeper - Iddra. Nice lady.
Shor's Stone - pissant little town, not even an inn. Just a bunch of miners scratching in the dirt.
<<Shared>> Hold on. This can get a bit tricky.
<<Shared>> That's Whiterun up on the hill there. We'll be at the main gate before you know it.
<<Shared>> That's Solitude just ahead. Only a few more minutes now.
<<Shared>> Ah, good. Markarth is just ahead. I'm glad to make it through the Reach one more time.
<<Shared>> Just a few more minutes and we'll be in Riften.
<<Shared>> We're almost there. Windhelm's just ahead.

Markarth is... different from the rest of Skyrim, there's no doubt about that. | The Reach has been part of Skyrim for a thousand years, but the Reachmen still haven't accepted it. | It was only 20 years back that the Reachmen rebelled. Even took control of Markarth itself for a time. | They were crushed, of course, but the survivors - the Forsworn - still lurk in the wilds and make the Reach dangerous for honest folk.
